Detailed Description

The route in text-form is inserted into a list of ExpandStringItems that is returned to the caller of the getStringDataItem()-method.

See also:
ExpandRouteReplyPacket For packet format.

DescProps ExpandStringItem::createRouteDescProps (  StringTable::languageCode  lang,
bool  compassLangShort,
byte  maxTurnNumbers,

StringTableUtility::distanceFormat  distFormat,
StringTableUtility::distanceUnit  distUnit,
bool  wapFormat,
ItemTypes::routedir_oddeven_t  oddevenstart,
ItemTypes::routedir_nbr_t  housenbrstart
)  [static]
 

Used to set the bitfield that describes the route description properties according to the specified parameters.

Parameters:
lang Language code of the route description.
compassLangShort If compass direction should be short.
maxTurnNumbers Maximum number of turns that should be printed out. Eg "turn left at the 9:th road".
printSignPostText Set this to true if signpost texts should be printed out.
distFormat Distance format used when printing the distance.
distUnit Measurment unit used when printing the distance. (Meters, feet or yards)
wapFormat Set this to true if the text should be wap formatted. All text that displayed on a wap phone must be formatted (for instance swedish characters must be replaced with escape-codes and so on).
oddevenstart The start direction for odd even house numbers.
housenbrstart The start direction for house numbers.
Returns:
The resulting uint32 describing the route description properties.

byte ExpandStringItem::getExitCount (   )  const [inline]
 

Get the exit count for this part of the route description.

The exit count describes the serial number of the street to turn into, e.g "2" here and "RIGHT" as getStringCode means "turn into the secon street on the right side".

Returns:
Exit count at the side described by getStringCode()

bool ExpandStringItem::getRouteDescription (  DescProps  descProps,
char *  buf,
uint32  maxLength,
uint32 &  nbrBytesWritten
)  const
 

Creates a route description, text formatted according to the specified route description properties bitfield.

For instance "Drive 660m then turn left into the third street Baravägen".

Parameters:
descProps Route description properties (bitfield) that that indicates which information that should be included in the route decription.
buf Preallocated buffer which will be filled with the routedescription.
maxLength The length of buf.
nbrBytesWritten The number of bytes written into buf.
Returns:
True if the route description did fit in the buffer, false otherwise.

int ExpandStringItem::getRouteDescriptionSMS (  StringTable::languageCode  language,
UserConstants::EOLType  eol,
int  maxLineLength,
char *  dest,
uint32  maxLength,
StringTableUtility::distanceUnit  distUnit = StringTableUtility::METERS
) 
 

Get this ExpandStringItem as text that should be inserted into an SMS.

Parameters:
language The prefered language of the route- description. Must be an SMS-language (e.g. SMSISH_ENG or SMSISH_SWE).
eol The type of end-o-line that should be used.
maxLineLength The maximum length of one row in the SMS.
dest A preallocated string where the result will be written.
maxLength The maximum number of characters to write to dest.
Returns:
The number of bytes written to dest, a negative value is returned upon error.
